<section id="workflowStep" role="standard">
  <title><indexterm significance="normal">
      <primary>workflow step, creating new</primary>
    </indexterm>Workflow Step</title>
  <para>To create a new workflow item, select the <guibutton>NEW</guibutton>
  button. The following screen will appear:<screenshot>
      <mediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata fileref="images/workflowStep.png"/>
        </imageobject>
        <caption>Workflow Step</caption>
      </mediaobject>
    </screenshot></para>
  <para>When defining workflow steps, you are presented with the following
  options:</para>
  <variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Module</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>Identify the module for the workflow.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Type</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>Specify the type for step. The type will change depending on the
        module selected.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Action</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>Select a standard action from the list of available actions.
        Standard actions are used to drive the activity list and open up
        screens automatically. The choices will vary depending on the module
        selected.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Name</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>Enter a name to describe the step.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Description</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>Enter a brief description of the step.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Priority</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>Specify the priority the step should be given.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Sequence</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>Specify the sequence order for the step.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Owner</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>Specify the owner of the step.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Assigned To</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>Specify the person the step should be assigned to.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Notification Profile</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>Select the EDI profile to be used for sending notifications to
        users when workflow activities are generated from the step.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Status</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>Specify the initial status of the step.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Start</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>Dates are used to define when a subsequent step must
        begin.</para>
        <variablelist>
          <varlistentry>
            <term>Calculate</term>
            <listitem>
              <para/>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
          <varlistentry>
            <term>Offset Days</term>
            <listitem>
              <para/>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
        </variablelist>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>End</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>Dates are used to define when a subsequent step must be
        completed.</para>
        <variablelist>
          <varlistentry>
            <term>Calculate</term>
            <listitem>
              <para/>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
          <varlistentry>
            <term>Offset Days</term>
            <listitem>
              <para/>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
        </variablelist>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Notes</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>An open text field for additional notes relating to the
        workflow</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>On Completion</term>
      <listitem>
        <para/>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
  <para>You are able to define next steps for when a workflow is complete and
  has passed or finished any requirements.</para>
  <para><screenshot>
      <mediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata fileref="images/workflowStepTabCompletion.png"/>
        </imageobject>
        <caption>On Completion tab</caption>
      </mediaobject>
    </screenshot></para>
  <variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Successors</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>The next step once the workflow is completed.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
  <para>You are able to define next steps for when a workflow has failed or
  has not been successfully completed. If it fails, there may be a next step.
  Multiple steps can be chained together. The options are dependent only on
  your business process.</para>
  <para><screenshot>
      <mediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata fileref="images/workflowStepTabDeferred.png"/>
        </imageobject>
        <caption>On Deferred tab</caption>
      </mediaobject>
    </screenshot></para>
  <variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Successors</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>The next step once the workflow is deferred.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
</section>
